WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.060
Thank you again for the invitation and to talk about Krenolanib.

00:00:06.280 --> 00:00:18.060
So this is the result of the ARO013 clinical trial evaluating Krenolanib plus intensive chemo in relapsed refractory EML.

00:00:18.900 --> 00:00:23.000
So as you know, Krenolanib is a type 1, 3 inhibitor.

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:36.740
So in the AIML in vitro assay, we observed a big sensitivity of Krenolanib for leukemic blasts with a flat rate mutation.

00:00:37.300 --> 00:00:47.980
And we also observed a highly active activity, again, blasts with a co-occurring mutation, NPM1, DNMT3A, TET2, and WT1.

00:00:47.980 --> 00:00:52.980
As you can see on the right, patient mutations.

00:00:53.000 --> 00:01:01.100
So patients who are mutated with FLT3 and NPM1 have a very high sensitivity with Krenolanib.

00:01:03.100 --> 00:01:06.100
So what we know about Krenolanib?

00:01:06.100 --> 00:01:18.100
So this is a high sensitivity drug for FLT3-mutated EML.

00:01:19.100 --> 00:01:22.100
We know that the Krenolanib does not accumulate.

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:31.000
And there is a similar drug level after day 1 to day 15.

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:38.000
There is favorable pharmacological properties with a short half time, 6 to 8 hours.

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:41.000
No significant drug-drug interaction.

00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:45.000
And there is no QT prolongation.

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:50.000
So today there is a big experience with Krenolanib.

00:01:50.000 --> 00:01:52.000
There is 375 patients.

00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:57.000
Already treated with Krenolanib in clinical trial.

00:01:57.000 --> 00:02:08.000
And the background of this study presented here was the phase 1 and phase 2 study, RO010 and RO011 study.

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:15.000
Where was evaluated a full dose of Krenolanib combined with intensive chemo.

00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:19.000
And the combination was safe.

00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:21.000
And we observed 67% of overall results.

00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:28.000
67% of overall response rate in relapsed refractory FLT3-mutated EML.

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:31.000
So this is the design of the clinical trial.

00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:35.000
So it was a randomized clinical trial, a one-to-one.

00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:44.000
Comparing salvaged chemo, flag-AIDA or AM, plus Krenolanib versus flag-AIDA or AM plus placebo.

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:49.000
The population was relapsed refractory, high-cute myeloid leukemia.

00:02:49.000 --> 00:03:00.000
Patient could have TKI treatment in first or second line.

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.000
And of course, all patients were mutated for FLT3.

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:10.000
So 106 patients were included in this clinical trial.

00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:13.000
The median age was 55.

00:03:13.000 --> 00:03:16.000
And 38% of patients

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:21.000
were more than 60 years old.

00:03:21.000 --> 00:03:30.000
93% of patients were mutated for FLT3 at Baseline.

00:03:30.000 --> 00:03:38.000
And 56% had co-occurring NPM1 mutations.

00:03:38.000 --> 00:03:45.000
So 100% of patients progressed after receiving intensive chemo in this clinical trial.

00:03:45.000 --> 00:03:50.000
27% progressed after two prior chemotherapy regimens.

00:03:50.000 --> 00:03:56.000
And 25% relapsed after prior allogeneic stem cell transplantation.

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:05.000
This is a population already exposed to FLT3 inhibitors.

00:04:05.000 --> 00:04:14.000
So 69% of patients already received at least one prior FLT3 TKI before entering in the trial.

00:04:14.000 --> 00:04:18.000
The majority was Midosterine.

00:04:18.000 --> 00:04:22.000
Some was Giltaritinib, usually at salvage as a second line.

00:04:22.000 --> 00:04:25.000
And few received Quisartinib and Sorafenib.

00:04:25.000 --> 00:04:35.000
So we observe in terms of response a significant increase of the overall response rate.

00:04:35.000 --> 00:04:42.000
So 39% to 60% using Crenolanib plus intensive chemo.

00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:47.000
So there is an increase in terms of response rate.

00:04:47.000 --> 00:04:51.000
But also a significant increase in terms of CRI.

00:04:53.000 --> 00:04:57.000
The primary endpoint of the study was the event-free survival.

00:04:57.000 --> 00:05:03.000
And we observe a significant increase of event-free survival in this clinical trial.

00:05:03.000 --> 00:05:08.000
There is a big improvement from 0 months to 3.4 months.

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:11.000
And in a post-hoc analysis,

00:05:11.000 --> 00:05:20.000
in patients commutated for NPM1 and FLT3,

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:24.000
it was 59 patients.

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:30.000
We observe also a significant increase in terms of event-free survival,

00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:33.000
but also in terms of overall survival.

00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:35.000
So for the overall survival,

00:05:35.000 --> 00:05:40.000
we observe an increase of 6 months to 12 months

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:43.000
using Crenolanib plus intensive chemo.

00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:52.000
For the patient breached to transplant after intensive chemo plus Crenolanib,

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:53.000
as you can see,

00:05:53.000 --> 00:06:00.000
we observe also a significant increase in terms of overall survival

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:03.000
after halostem cell transplantation.

00:06:03.000 --> 00:06:09.000
We could use Crenolanib as maintenance after halostem cell transplantation.

00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:13.000
In this specific clinical trial,

00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:17.000
and you can see for the patient treated with salvage chemo plus Crenolanib,

00:06:17.000 --> 00:06:19.000
the median overall survival was not rich.

00:06:21.000 --> 00:06:23.000
In terms of safety,

00:06:23.000 --> 00:06:30.000
so we observe the same safety already observed in the other clinical trial.

00:06:30.000 --> 00:06:33.000
So the drug was manageable.

00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:38.000
The main side effect was the GI toxicity.

00:06:38.000 --> 00:06:42.000
GI toxicity with nausea and diarrhea.

00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:46.000
But you can see this is manageable.

00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:52.000
This is more a grade 1 and grade 2 severity.

00:06:54.000 --> 00:06:56.000
So to conclude,

00:06:56.000 --> 00:07:02.000
so this is the first randomized trial demonstrating the benefits

00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:07.000
to add 3TKI to intensive chemo

00:07:07.000 --> 00:07:12.000
in this specific setting in relapsed refractory EML.

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:22.000
This is the first randomized trial showing also that we can use

00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:30.000
a new 3TKI after a first one and two increased survival.

00:07:30.000 --> 00:07:36.000
And there is a specific benefit in subpopulation mutated

00:07:36.000 --> 00:07:41.000
with NPM1 and FLT3 mutation.

00:07:41.000 --> 00:07:45.000
So I would like to thank all the patients and family

00:07:45.000 --> 00:07:48.000
and all investigators implicated in this study.

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:50.000
Thank you for your attention.
